column5: Well we heard of him arriving safely along the way to the BOQ, has anyone heard from him on his trip home?  When did he leave Merlands?  Maureen

Glen left Merland Park around 11 am on Sunday morning.  He seemed refreshed, with intelligent plans to take it easy on the way home, even spending the night in a hotel.  With a total driving time of about 22 hours, we might see a post from him late tonight, but more likely sometime tomorrow.
I tried his cell phone all day but it wasn't working for me.I may have an old number for him.If anyone has his cell number PM me and I'll give him a call.I'm sure he is fine. Joe
Here I is! Here I is! Here I is!!!  Just got in a couple hours ago, all safe and sound!  That 2 day drive one way is a real Butt-Kicker!!!
Good to see you made it..whats up with yer cell phone? Joe
Glad to see you made it home safe and sound Dawg...now where's that report  Maureen
He is probably sorting through all the pics of us Hosers right now
Glad you're home safe, Bubba. Catch you soon.
